maml:description.maml:para: This cmdlet establishes a connection to a VMware VCF Installer Server.

This cmdlet establishes a connection to a VMware VCF Installer Server. The resulting connections are added to the list of default connections in a global variable named "$global:defaultInstallerConnections" (if the NotDefault switch was not specified).
Specifies the IP address or fully qualified domain name (FQDN) of the VMware VCF Installer Server.
Specifies the user name to log in to the VMware VCF Installer Server.
Specifies the password to log in to the VMware VCF Installer Server.
Specifies the credentials to log in to the VMware VCF Installer Server. You can use this parameter as an alternative to the User/Password parameter pair.
If specified, PowerCLI ignores any errors related to invalid server certificates of the VMware VCF Installer Server.
If specified, the resulting connection is not recorded in the list of default VMware VCF Installer server connections and must be manually specified when you use a cmdlet.
Specifies the port on the server you want to use for the connection. If not specified, a protocol-specific default value is used.
Specifies the Internet protocol you want to use for the connection. It can be either HTTP or HTTPS. If not specified, HTTPS is used.
